text: The Prime Minister is putting a spotlight on Australia's relationship with the United States ahead of the Liberal Party's 75th anniversary. Scott Morrison declared signing the ANZUS treaty as the "single most important achievement" of the Liberal party in government, which formalises the United States' security presence in the Pacific. Mr Morrison told the Australian the Liberals can be trusted to deliver safety, stability and prosperity for all. In the interview marking the party's anniversary, the prime minister reflected on his own political journey and compared it with former Prime Ministers John Howard and Sir Robert Menzies.
